er page.',0,NULL,0,7,21),(6672,3,'wcf.acp.option.search_use_captcha','Search',0,NULL,0,7,21),(6673,3,'wcf.acp.option.search_use_captcha.description','',0,NULL,0,7,21),(6674,3,'wcf.acp.package.step.install.SearchableMessageTypePip','Installing searchable message types ...',0,NULL,0,8,21),(6675,3,'wcf.acp.package.step.uninstall.SearchableMessageTypePip','Uninstalling searchable message types ...',0,NULL,0,8,21),(6676,3,'wcf.acp.package.step.update.SearchableMessageTypePip','Updating searchable message types ...',0,NULL,0,8,21),(6677,3,'wcf.help.item.search','Search',0,NULL,0,24,21),(6678,3,'wcf.help.item.search.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"{@RELATIVE_WCF_DIR}images/help/helpSearch1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Search Drop Down</span></p><p>There is a handy search field on the top of each page, which adapts its functions dynamically to the page you\'re currently browsing. The search function only searches the area where you currently are, so if you are reading a thread using the search will search this very thread only. If you want to search the whole forum you will have to search from the start page. The search field also holds a dropdown menu with some frequently used search options, as well as a link to the <a href=\"index.php?form=Search{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Extended Search</a> interface, which offers many advanced search options.</p>\n<h4>Search options</h4>\n<p>Use the following options to search more efficiently.</p>\n<div class=\"border\">\n	<table class=\"tableList\">\n		<thead>\n			<tr class=\"tableHead\">\n				<th><div><span class=\"emptyHead\">Term</span></div></th>\n				<th><div><span class=\"emptyHead\">Description</span></div></th>\n			</tr>\n		</thead>\n		<tbody>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>Text*</code></td>\n				<td>The Asterisk is a wildcard, which means e.g. &quot;Textbla&quot; will also be found. This operator may only be used at the end of a word.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>+Text</code></td>\n				<td>Terms with a leading plus have to be found.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>-Text</code></td>\n				<td>You can also exclude certain terms from your search by adding a minus sign.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>Text Text2</code></td>\n				<td>If you just write the words, every possibilitiy will be listed, even if only one of those terms is found. Results containing both terms will be listed topmost.</td></tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>&gt;Text &lt;Text2</code></td>\n				<td>With the arrow operator you can weight a certain term, which will then be more important within the search results.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>+Text +(&gt;Text2 &lt;Text3)</code></td>\n				<td>You can also use brackets to make sub-searches. The example will list results including &quot;Text&quot; and &quot;Text2&quot; or &quot;Text&quot; and &quot;Text3&quot;. The terms called first will have a greater importance.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>+Text ~Text2</code></td>\n				<td>The tilde allows you to negate the priority. Results including &quot;Text&quot; and &quot;Text2&quot; will not have a lower priority if &quot;Text2&quot; is not included.</td></tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>&quot;Text Text2&quot;</code></td>\n				<td>The double quotemark allows you to highlight certain word groups. The search-results will then only include results where the whole word-group appears. &quot;Text, Text2&quot; for example will not be found, because there is a comma in between, which was not entered as phrase.</td>\n			</tr>\n		</tbody>\n	</table>\n</div>\n<p>You can also search for an author and limit the time frame of the search results. Specify also the area to be searched.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,21),(6679,3,'wcf.search.author','Search by author',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6680,3,'wcf.search.error.noMatches','There are no results for your search &quot;{$query}&quot;.',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6681,3,'wcf.search.error.user.noMatches','There are no results from this author.',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6682,3,'wcf.search.general','General search terms',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6683,3,'wcf.search.period','In time period',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6684,3,'wcf.search.period.end','until:',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6685,3,'wcf.search.period.start','from:',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6686,3,'wcf.search.query','Search by key words',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6687,3,'wcf.search.query.description','Enter one or more terms. One term has to contain at least four characters.{if MODULE_HELP} All search possibilities you can find within <a href=\"index.php?page=Help&amp;item=search{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">the help</a>.{/if}',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6688,3,'wcf.search.results','Search results',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6689,3,'wcf.search.results.change','Change search',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6690,3,'wcf.search.results.description','Search results {#$startIndex}-{#$endIndex} of {#$items}{if $query} for &quot;<strong>{$query}</strong>&quot;{/if}.{if $items == 1000} There are even more results, please redefine your search.{/if}{if $highlight}<br />These search terms are highlighted: <span class=\"highlight\">{$highlight}</span>{/if}',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6691,3,'wcf.search.results.display','Display',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6692,3,'wcf.search.results.location','found in:',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6693,3,'wcf.search.sortBy','Sort by',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6694,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.author','Author',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6695,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.creationDate','Date',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6696,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.relevance','Relevance',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6697,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.subject','Subject',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6698,3,'wcf.search.subjectOnly','Only search in subject line',0,NULL,0,4