he user online record?',0,NULL,0,7,27),(11814,3,'wcf.acp.option.visit_time_frame','Automatic &quot;Mark as read&quot;',0,NULL,0,7,27),(11815,3,'wcf.acp.option.visit_time_frame.description','Enter the number of seconds after which threads should be marked as read.',0,NULL,0,7,27),(11816,3,'wcf.acp.stats.type.post','Posts',0,NULL,0,77,27),(11817,3,'wcf.acp.stats.type.thread','Threads',0,NULL,0,77,27),(11818,3,'wcf.attachment.containerType.post','Post',0,NULL,0,26,27),(11819,3,'wcf.help.item.board','Forum',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11820,3,'wcf.help.item.board.board','Boards and categories',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11821,3,'wcf.help.item.board.board.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpBoardBoard1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Board list</span></p>\n<p>The board index shows all viewable boards and categories. Below the board list there is the option to mark all boards as read with a single click.</p>\n<h4>Board</h4>\n<p>A board is a place where different topics (called threads) can be discussed. In front of the boardname you will find an icon that displays the status of a board. Behind the boardname the number in brackets shows how many threads are unread. A doubleclick on the icon marks all threads as read within this board. Additional information can be displayed - such as a description of the board, subboards, moderators or the users that are currently browsing this board.</p>\n<ul class=\"dataList\">\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}boardM.png{/icon}\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Regular board</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">This symbolises a regular board with no new posts.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}boardNewM.png{/icon}\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Board with new posts</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">The board contains new, unread posts. A doubleclick on that icon marks all threads as read within this board.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}boardClosedM.png{/icon}\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Closed board (Archive)</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">This board is readonly.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Categories</h4>\n<p>Categories can contain different boards to group them by topic. They are highlighted with an own background color and can be opened or closed. Closed categories may also have a number in brackets that tells if there are unread posts within the whole category. No threads can be opened directly in a category.</p>\n<h4>External link</h4>\n<p>Within the board index there may be some links to external pages.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11822,3,'wcf.help.item.board.description','<p>In the following part you will get a short introduction into the most important features of the board, including the threads and posts, favorites as well as boards and categories</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11823,3,'wcf.help.item.board.subscription','Favorites',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11824,3,'wcf.help.item.board.subscription.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpBoardSubscription1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Favorite thread</span></p>\n<p>You can add boards and threads to your favorites. On the bottom of a board or thread there is the link to add or remove your favorite. You will then receive a notification e-mail in case of new posts or threads. Only one e-mail will be send each favorite. So you need to visit the board or thread in order to get new notification e-mails.</p>\n<p>Within <a href=\"index.php?form=UserProfileEdit{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Edit Profile</a> &raquo; Management &raquo; <a href=\"index.php?page=SubscriptionsList{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Favorites</a> you can get an overview about all favorites. You can also remove them from your list.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11825,3,'wcf.help.item.board.thread','Threads and posts',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11826,3,'wcf.help.item.board.thread.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpBoardThread1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Thread list</span></p>\n<p>The thread list contains the threads of a selected forum. The threads may be separated into important threads or announcements and normal threads. Clicking the table head the threads can be sorted.</p>\n<p>Below the thread list there are several filter and sorting options. It is possible for example that there are no threads to display because of a filter setting: Show only threads of the last 30 days. The icon of a thread symbolises the status of a thread. Please note that different status combinations are possible:</p>\n<ul class=\"dataList\">\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}threadM.png{/icon}\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Read</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">You have already read this thread.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}threadNewM.png{/icon}\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Unread</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">If a thread contains unread posts it is displayed bold. In front of the thread name is an arrow icon that takes you to the first unread post within the thread. A doubleclick on the thread icon will mark the thread as read.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}threadClosedM.png{/icon}\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Closed</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">Threads may be closed by moderators, replies are then no longer possible.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}threadM.png{/icon}\" style=\"opacity: 0.5\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Disabled</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">The administrator can set certain forums moderated, meaning that threads are marked disabled after they are created. A moderator has to enable the thread first to make it accessible by other users. Moderators will see those disabled threads marked green.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<div class=\"containerIcon\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"{icon}threadTrashM.png{/icon}\" style=\"opacity: 0.5\" /></div>\n		<div class=\"containerContent\">\n			<h5>Deleted</h5>\n			<p class=\"smallFont\">Deleted threads will be marked red and stay visible for moderators only until they are removed completely.</p>\n		</div>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you click on one of the threads you will see the posts of this thread. There are displayed together with information about their authors.</p>\n<h4>Additional information</h4>\n<ul>\n	{if $allItemNames[\'message\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=message{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Writing text</a></li>{/if}\n	{if $allItemNames[\'message.editor\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=message.editor{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Editor</a></li>{/if}\n	{if $allItemNames[\'message.smiley\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=message.smiley{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Smileys</a></li>{/if}\n	{if $allItemNames[\'message.bbcode\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=message.bbcode{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">BBCodes</a></li>{/if}\n	{if $allItemNames[\'message.attachment\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=message.attachment{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Attachments</a></li>{/if}\n	{if $allItemNames[\'message.quote\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=message.quote{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Quotes</a></li>{/if}\n	{if $allItemNames[\'moderation.thread\']|isset}<li><a href=\"index.php?page=Help&item=moderation.thread{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">Moderation</a></li>{/if}\n</ul>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11827,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread','Threads and posts',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11828,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThread1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Thread moderation</span></p>\n<p>There are two possible ways to edit threads and posts:</p>\n<ol>\n	<li>To edit a single thread or post you just need to click on the related icon. It should have a little arrow to indicate a popup menu. The menu has all options to edit this thread or post.</li>\n	<li>If you want to edit several posts or threads at once you need to select them with their related checkboxes (<input type=\"checkbox\" />). If you have selected five threads for example there will be a button with the label &quot;5 marked threads&quot; at the bottom of the page. A click on that button opens a menu with options you can execute on the selected threads. You can bulk edit posts the same way.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Please note that not all options are available in both - the single and the bulk editing.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11829,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.close','Open / close post/thread',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11830,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.close.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadClose1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Close thread</span></p>\n<p>Threads that are closed cannot get a new reply by normal users. Closed posts cannot be edited by the author anymore. A thread or post that is closed will be marked with a little lock on the icon.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11831,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.delete','Delete / recover post/thread',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11832,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.delete.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadDelete1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Delete thread</span></p>\n<p>You can delete threads. As long as a thread is still within the recycle bin you can recover it.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11833,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.disable','Enable / Disable post/thread',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11834,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.disable.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadDisable1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Enable thread</span></p>\n<p>This options is used if a forum is set moderated. Threads then have to be enabled by moderators first before they can be seen by all users.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11835,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.editPost','Edit post',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11836,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.editPost.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadEditPost1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Edit post</span></p>\n<p>To change the content of a post you need to click on the &quot;Edit&quot; button of the related post or select the option within the edit menu of that post.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11837,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.editPrefix','Edit prefix',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11838,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.editPrefix.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadEditPrefix1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Edit prefix</span></p>\n<p>There are two ways as well: You can use the edit menu or doubleclick on an existing prefix (only if there is one).</p>\n<p>The administrator must have set up prefixes for this board if you want to use or edit them.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11839,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.editTitle','Edit title',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11840,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.editTitle.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadEditTitle1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Edit title</span></p>\n<p>You can change the title of a post directly within the thread list, simply click the icon to select the option within the menu or doubleclick onto the title.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11841,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.movePost','Move post',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11842,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.movePost.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadMovePost1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Move post</span></p>\n<p>If you want to extract posts of a thread because they don\'t have anything to do with the thread you need to select these posts. You can now go to another thread  or to a thread list. On the bottom of the page you will find the button to edit the selected posts. The following options can be found if click on that button on a thread list:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Create new thread (move post)</h5>\n		<p>The marked posts will be moved into a separate thread.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Create new thread (copy posts)</h5>\n		<p>The marked threads will be moved into a new thread, but the posts will be kept in the original thread.</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you enter another thread you will get these options when you click on the bulk edit button:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Move here</h5>\n		<p>The selected posts will be extracted from their original thread and moved into the current thread.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Copy here</h5>\n		<p>The selected posts will be only copied to the current thread but they remain in their old thread as well.</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11843,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.moveThread','Move thread',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11844,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.moveThread.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadMoveThread1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Move thread</span></p>\n<p>If a thread has been created in a wrong board you can move it. Select the thread and open the board you want to move it. On the bottom of the page you will find the button with the bulk edit menu. If you click on it you have the choice between:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Move here</h5>\n		<p>You can move all selected threads into a different forum. All threads will be deleted in the old forum and moved into the new one.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Move here (including link)</h5>\n		<p>All threads will be moved like on &quot;Move here&quot; but there will be a link to the moved post on the old forum. Those links have to be deleted manually.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Copy here</h5>\n		<p>The selected threads will be copied to the current board but they remain in their old board. The copy is a new thread and has nothing to do anymore with the old thread.</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you open the bulk edit menu within another thread you will get these options:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Merge thread</h5>\n		<p>The selected threads will be merged with the current thread. The old threads will be deleted.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n		<h5>Copy and merge thread</h5>\n		<p>The selected threads will be merged with the current thread. The old threads will be left untouched.</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11845,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.stick','Stick / Unstick thread',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11846,3,'wcf.help.item.moderation.thread.stick.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"images/help/helpModerationThreadStick1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Stick thread</span></p>\n<p>If you want to add a thread to the important threads of a board you need to select this option in the menu. The same way you can remove a thread from the important threads.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,27),(11847,3,'wcf.search.type.post','Forums',0,NULL,0,47,27),(11848,3,'wcf.tagging.taggable.all.com.woltlab.wbb.thread','All threads',0,NULL,0,78,27),(11849,3,'wcf.tagging.taggable.com.woltlab.wbb.thread','Threads',0,NULL,0,78,27),(11850,3,'wcf.user.moderatedBoards','Moderated forums',0,NULL,0,17,27),(11851,3,'wcf.user.posts','Posts',0,NULL,0,17,27),(11852,3,'wcf.user.postsPerDay','({$posts} Posts per day)',0,NULL,0,17,27),(11853,3,'wcf.user.option.enableEmailNotification','E-mail notification on new post in favorites',0,NULL,0,18,27),(11854,3,'wcf.user.option.enableEmailNotification.description','',